      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "9275102e-b15b-4672-b8e8-c0033bc4145e",
      "text": "Project Cybersyn was a Chilean project from 1971–1973 during the presidency of Salvador Allende aimed at constructing a distributed decision support system to aid in the management of the national economy. The project consisted of four modules: an economic simulator, custom software to check factory performance, an operations room, and a national network of telex machines that were linked to one mainframe computer - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Project_Cybersyn wikipedia]"
